cello.alt.servlet.script
Class JavaScriptResource

java.lang.Object
  cello.alt.servlet.script.JavaScriptResource
All Implemented Interfaces:
MutableResource, Resource, JavaScript
public class JavaScriptResource
extends java.lang.Object
implements JavaScript, MutableResource

This AbstractJavaScript class a useful basis for creating cached JavaScript classes. It implements all the necessary dependency loading/updating and only requires two methods to be implemented (isModified and evaluate).

Author:
Marcello

getVersionTag

public java.lang.Object getVersionTag()
Description copied from interface: MutableResource
Returns some object to specify the current version of this Resource. This could be as simple as a modification timestamp or some sort of version number. Since this method could potentially be called frequently (every time the resource is needed), efficiency is recommended. Recommended usage of this method involves comparing the current result with a previously cached result using Object.equals(java.lang.Object).

Specified by:

addDependency

public void addDependency(JavaScript dependency,
                          boolean cascadeReload)
Adds this script as a dependency of this object. The dependency can be added as a "cascade" dependency. When a cascade dependency is modified, the current script is also reevaluated (even if it is not modified).

Specified by:
addDependency in interface JavaScript
Parameters:
dependency - the JavaScript you depend on
cascadeReload - whether or not to cascade the reload
